#!/usr/bin/env bash

set -euo pipefail

backup_dir="${HOME}/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/Raycast"

mkdir -p "$backup_dir" 2>/dev/null || true
open -a Raycast 2>/dev/null || true

cat <<EOF
Raycast backup is app-driven.

On the old Mac:
1. In Raycast, run "Export Settings & Data".
2. Set or confirm an export passphrase.
3. Save the encrypted .rayconfig file in:
   ${backup_dir}

On the new Mac, rerun ./bin/setup or ./bin/raycast-restore after iCloud syncs the export.

Raycast encrypts .rayconfig exports, but they still contain app settings and extension state.
Keep the export and passphrase outside git; store the passphrase in Keychain or another private store.
EOF
